  "texts": [
    "Despite these limitations, the study contributes insights into the performance trade-offs between encoder and decoder architectures in specific NLU tasks, offering a foundation for future research with broader considerations.In this work, we have answered the question of whether the large scale of newer LLMs is required for real-world applications, or if smaller, yet proficient encoder-only models can provide pragmatic and resource-efficient solutions.",
    "We have compared the performance of the encoder-only model with that of newer decoder-only architectures using different approaches.",
    "We have evidenced that smaller encoder-only models outperforms larger decoder-only models in intent classification task, and score close to them in sentiment analysis.",
    "The additional operational cost required by decoder-only models make the architecture decision oriented towards encoder-only models for natural language understanding tasks.Table 11Datasets used and their characteristics.",
